OL,3,CFormer justice secretary warned Sunak
OL,4,Cof a 'pray date' on prison overcrowding
OL,6,FChalk had warned for some time that
OL,7,Fthe system was reaching tipping point
OL,8,Fbut would then use short term measures
OL,9,Flike ESCL ( End of Custody Supervised
OL,10,FLicence) to ease the pressure.
OL,12,FThat would not require legislation but
OL,13,Fwould mean some prisoners would be
OL,14,Freleased 18 days earlier.
OL,16,FBecause of the success of ESCL there
OL,17,Fwas a sense in Downing Street that the
OL,18,FMoJ was 'crying wolf', according to
OL,19,Fsources, and so they were reluctant to
OL,20,Ftake action as Chalk became more
OL,21,Finsistent.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
