OL,6,FOne probation officer speaking
OL,7,Fanonymously said they feared there was
OL,8,Fa risk because the system had been so
OL,9,Fbadly run down.
OL,11,FThey said the answer was more resource
OL,12,Ffor the probation system.
OL,14,FMahmood said anyone at risk of
OL,15,Fhomelessness would get 12 weeks of
OL,16,Faccommodation - including the
OL,17,Fpossibility of using budget hotels,
OL,18,Fwhich could be controversial.
